{{Infobox person | name = Jayson Gaignard | image = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | birth_name = | death_date = | death_place = | residence = | nationality = [[Canadians|Canadian]] | education = | occupation = Author, entrepreneur | known_for = Founder of MastermindTalks | ethnicity = | religion = | networth = | children = 1 daughter<ref name="entrepreneur">Kugler, Logan [http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/246665 How This Entrepreneur Went From Dead Broke to Mega Influencer in One Year] ''Entrepreneur''. December 11, 2015</ref> | spouse = | parents = | family = | website = [http://www.mastermindtalks.com/ MastermindTalks.com] }}
'''Jayson Gaignard''' is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[entrepreneurship|entrepreneur]], networking specialist, and [[author]] who founded MastermindTalks, an invitation-only conference for entrepreneurs, in 2013.<ref name="F1">Corcoran, John [https://www.forbes.com/sites/johncorcoran/2015/01/08/25-professional-networking-experts-to-watch-in-2015/2/ 25 Professional Networking Experts to Watch in 2015] ''Forbes.'' December 14, 2015</ref><ref>[http://notable.ca/jayson-gaignard-todays-notable-young-entrepreneur/ Jayson Gaignard: Today’s Notable Young Entrepreneur] ''Notable''. December 14, 2015</ref><ref>Lui, Herbert [http://lifehacker.com/beyond-event-hopping-how-to-step-up-your-professional-1657396328?newstream=off Beyond Event Hopping: How to Step Up Your Professional Networking] ''LifeHacker''. December 15, 2015</ref><ref>Rose, Jeff [http://www.dailyfinance.com/2014/12/19/5networking-mistakes/ 5 Networking Strategies You Are Doing Flat-Out Wrong] ''Daily Finance''. December 15, 2015</ref>
==Background==
Gaignard dropped out of high school at the age of 17 and began working as an [[auto mechanic]].<ref name="entrepreneur" /> In 2004, Gaignard founded VIP Services Inc., a [[Toronto]]-based full-service [[concierge]] company.<ref name="concierge">Pachner, Joanna [http://www.nationalpost.com/concierge+seasons+decline+yourself+rise+services/200921/story.html A concierge for all seasons: the decline of do-it-yourself, and the rise of do-it-for-me services] ''National Post''. December 15, 2015</ref><ref>Vermond, Kira [https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/a-holiday-from-heavy-lifting/article709562/ A holiday from heavy lifting] ''Globe and Mail''. December 15, 2015</ref> The company evolved into an online ticket seller and changed its name to Tickets Canada, which generated $5 million in annual sales.<ref name="entrepreneur" />
==MastermindTalks==
In 2012, Gaignard began curating dinners in Toronto, Canada with small groups of entrepreneurs that focused on relationship building.<ref name="entrepreneur" /> The invite-only dinners became MastermindTalks—larger conferences for entrepreneurs geared toward health, wealth, self-improvement, and networking.<ref name="F1" /><ref name="Lui">Lui, Herbert [http://www.techvibes.com/blog/lessons-mastermindtalks-2013-05-28 Three Essential Lessons from MastermindTalks] ''TechVibes''. December 15, 2015</ref><ref name="FP">Spence, Rick [http://business.financialpost.com/entrepreneur/5-lessons-from-the-masterminds-an-inside-look-at-entrepreneurs-elite-conference 5 lessons from the Masterminds: An inside look at entrepreneurs’ elite conference] ''Financial Post''. December 14, 2015</ref> Past MastermindTalks speakers include [[Tim Ferriss]], [[James Altucher]], [[A. J. Jacobs]], [[Esther Perel]], [[Dave Asprey]], [[Guy Kawasaki]], and [[Marc Ecko]].<ref name="Lui" /><ref name="FP" /><ref>Turner, Matthew [http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/246627 3 Ways to Wring Great Ideas From Mistakes] ''Entrepreneur''. December 14, 2015</ref> [[Forbes Magazine|Forbes]] described Gaignard as one of the top networkers to watch in 2015.<ref>Hall, Jason [https://www.forbes.com/sites/johnhall/2015/03/01/conferences-that-will-keep-you-ahead-of-marketing-trends-this-year/ Marketing Conferences That Will Keep You Ahead Of Trends in 2015] ''Forbes''. December 15, 2015</ref>
