{{for|the Australian footballer|Dick Burrows}} {{Infobox person | name = Richard Burrows | image = | caption = | birth_name = Richard George William Burrows | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1946|01|16}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | nationality = Irish | ethnicity = | education = [[Wesley College (Dublin)]] | alma_mater = | occupation = Businessman | years_active = 1967–present | salary = $671,423 | title = Chairman of [[British American Tobacco]] | term = 2009–present | predecessor = [[Jan du Plessis]] | successor = '''Incumbent''' | boards = [[Rentokil Initial]], [[CityJet]], [[Carlsberg Group]], [[Pernod Ricard]]<ref name="BW_01">{{cite web|url=http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=1466413&ticker=BATS:LN&previousCapId=326614&previousTitle=British%20American%20Tobacco%20plc | title=Executive Profile: Richard Burrows |publisher=Business Week |date=|accessdate=9 December 2012}}</ref> | spouse = | children = }}
'''Richard George William Burrows''' (born 16 January 1946) is an Irish businessman. He is the chairman of [[British American Tobacco]] plc (informally BAT), the world's second-largest tobacco company by sales, and chief executive of [[Irish Distillers]].<ref name= Offer >{{citenews | url=http://www.independent.ie/business/world/reynolds-american-wants-bat-to-up-offer-35219289.html | title= Reynolds American wants BAT to up offer | newspaper= Business World | date= November 16, 2016 | last= David | first= Ruth | accessdate= November 23, 2016}}</ref> In October 2016, Burrows became the chairman of Craven House Capital, an AIM-listed company that specializes in restructuring, expansion and turnaround investments in crisis and transitioning economics.<ref name= Craven>{{citenews | url= https://www.businesspost.ie/business/richard-burrows-becomes-chair-of-craven-house-capital-336528 | title= Richard Burrows becomes chair of Craven House Capital | newspaper= The Business Post | date= October 9, 2016 | last= Burke | first= Rolsin | accessdate= November 23, 2016}}</ref>
==Early life== Burrows is a graduate of [[Wesley College (Dublin)]].
==Career== Burrows joined the board of British American Tobacco plc as a non-executive director in September 2009 and became chairman on 1 November 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bat.com/group/sites/uk__3mnfen.nsf/vwPagesWebLive/DO7V2QY7?opendocument&SKN=1 | title=BAT>About us>Board of Directors: Richard Burrows, Chairman |publisher=BAT |date=|accessdate=30 October 2012}}</ref>
Burrows was formerly Governor of the [[Bank of Ireland]], a post he resigned from in June 2009.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2010/nov/26/bank-of-ireland-former-boss | title=Ireland bailout: Banker who got out just in time |publisher=The Guardian |date=26 November 2010|accessdate=30 October 2012 |location=London |first=Richard |last=Wachman}}</ref>
==Honours and awards== In June 1996, he was made a Chevalier of the French [[Legion of Honour]].<ref name="BW_01" />
